lighting theoretical puzzles, analysing broad historical perspectives and addressing contemporary challenges. In bringing the sea back into IR, the book reconceptualises the canvas of international relations to include the oceans as a social, political, economic and military space which affects the workings of world politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGeopolitics. 0aInternational relations. 0aOceanxPolitical aspects. 4aPolitical Studies 2022. 70(DE-588)4003846-40(DE-627)10438896X0(DE-576)208852972aAußenpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4006292-20(DE-627)10637804X0(DE-576)208864989aBevölkerungsentwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4020216-10(DE-627)1043942850(DE-576)208932429aGeografie2gnd 70(DE-588)4038301-50(DE-627)1044439520(DE-576)209029420aMeer2gnd 70(DE-588)4046514-70(DE-627)1041522060(DE-576)209069945aPolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4054184-80(DE-627)1061636390(DE-576)209107758aSeeschifffahrt2gnd 70(DE-588)4054790-50(DE-627)1061610750(DE-576)209110589aSicherheit2gnd 70(DE-588)4072885-70(DE-627)1060939320(DE-576)209188553aInternationale Politik2gnd 70(DE-588)4156686-50(DE-627)1055065400(DE-576)209828730aGeografischer Raum2gnd 70(DE-588)4156741-90(DE-627)1046090010(DE-576)209829168aGeopolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4209283-80(DE-627)1043532010(DE-576)210191112aEinflussgröße2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aanthropocene.  afishing.  alaw of the sea.  amaritime security.  anational identity.  aoceans.  apiracy.  aprivateering.  asea.  athalassocracy.1 a Colás, Alejandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraarud, Filippa Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarvalho, Benjamin de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarvalho, Benjam